<h1>Task Description <small>What is this task all about?</small></h1>
</div>
This data collection task is part of our research project that aims to determine Citation Provenance (read more on the <a href="/about">purpose</a> of the project). The task, is to annotate scientific papers, capturing information leading to the information referred to by the citation (i.e. cited information).
<p>
<h2>Task Objective</h2>
<p>
The objective of this task is to gather manual annotations for our research. We wish to annotate whether a citation is <strong>General</strong>, <strong>Specific</strong> or <strong>Undetermined</strong>.
</p>
<div class="row">
<div class="span4">
<div class="alert alert-success">
<h3>General</h3>
<p>A <strong>General</strong> citation simply means Paper A is citing Paper B in general. Paper A is making reference to Paper B as a whole, or simply giving credit for the work done by authors of Paper B.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="span4">
<div class="alert alert-success">
<h3>Specific</h3>
<p>A <strong>Specific</strong> citation means Paper A is making reference to a <strong>specific</strong> section of Paper B. For instance, Paper A makes reference to a particular system, System ABC, created/described by Paper B in Paper B's second section (e.g. Our System). Since Paper A is specifically referring to this section of the paper, we say this cite is specific.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="span4">
<div class="alert alert-success">
<h3>Undetermined</h3>
<p>In cases where it is not possible to determine the type of the citation.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Task Requirements</h2>
<p>
A participant, provided with a set of scientific papers, need to determine the type of citation, and to annotate with details about the citation. To do so, the participant needs to refer to the <strong>citing sentence</strong> in the citing paper, and attempt to locate the <strong>cited information</strong> in the cited paper. If you're ready, go on to <a href="./home#Annotate">How To Annotate</a>.
</p>
